            "client": "website",
            "content": "<p>I couldn't figure out how to install Statistical Rethinking's <code>rethinking</code> library on macOS high sierra (something with rstan), but I managed to get things working in Docker:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>FROM rocker/r-apt:xenial\n\nRUN apt-get update \\\n  &amp;&amp; apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    curl \\\n    libedit2 \\\n    openssl \\\n    psmisc \\\n    r-cran-coda \\\n    r-cran-devtools \\\n    r-cran-loo \\\n    r-cran-mvtnorm \\\n    r-cran-rstan \\\n    sudo \\\n  # Install rstudio itself.\n  &amp;&amp; wget https://download2.rstudio.org/rstudio-server-1.1.419-amd64.deb \\\n  &amp;&amp; dpkg -i rstudio-server-1.1.419-amd64.deb \\\n  # Add a non-root user for rstudio\n  &amp;&amp; useradd rstudio \\\n  &amp;&amp; echo &quot;rstudio:rstudio&quot; | chpasswd \\\n  &amp;&amp; mkdir /home/rstudio &amp;&amp; chown rstudio:rstudio /home/rstudio \\\n  &amp;&amp; addgroup rstudio staff \\\n  # And finally install `rethinking`.\n  &amp;&amp; R -e &#39;devtools::install_github(&quot;rmcelreath/rethinking&quot;)&#39;\n\nEXPOSE 8787\n\nCMD [&quot;bash&quot;]\n</pre></div>",
